description.et:
Kursuse hõlmatav temaatika:

1.	autoriõiguse ja IKT vastandus;
        *	autoriõiguse põhiprintsiibid (sh tarkvara ja andmebaaside õiguslik kaitse);
        *	õiguste teostamine (nt vaba kasutus, digiõiguste haldus (DRM));
        *	autoriõigusega kaitstud teoste kasutamine (nt vastavalt seadusele, lepingule, Creative Commons'ile); tasulised ja tasuta tarkvaralitsentsid (BSD, GPL, MIT);

2.	tööstusomand;
        *	kaubamärkide, t;;stusdisainide, patentide ja domeeninimede õiguslike režiimide põhiprintsiibid;

3.	intellektuaalomandi õiguse jõustamine infoajastul;
        *	praktiline teave intellektuaalomandi IT õigusega seotud kohtumenetlusest;
        *	riiklike ning rahvusvaheliste kohtute ja muude organite kohtupraktika (nt Euroopa Ühenduste Kohus);

4.	intellektuaalomandi- ja IT-õiguse tulevik;
        *	õiguste halduse ja jõustamise võimalik edu või ebaõnnestumine jne.

Assessment criteria for oral assignments:
- correctness of formalization and compliance with the requirements;
- level of analysis, establishing connections, level of interpretation;
- logic and integrity of covering the subject;
- Answering to the questions is assessed.

Level "E": the assignment is in compliance with the requirements; references and the elements of analysis and independent interpreting are there; the coverage of the subject is logical and corresponds to the demands of legal writing.

Assessment criteria for written assignments:
- correctness of formalization and compliance with the requirements;
- relevance and extent of references;
- level of analysis, establishing connections, level of interpretation;
- logic and integrity of covering the subject;
- in case of test, the correctness of answers.

Level "E": the assignment is in compliance with the requirements; references and the elements of analysis and independent interpreting are there; the coverage of the subject is logical and corresponds to the demands of legal writing.

grade_evaluation.et:
The aspects of performance of the student that are assessed are the following (for the final result, all parts are added together):

- Written homework 1 (copyright): 20%;
- Written homework 2 (industrial property): 20%
- Test 20%;
- Moot Court submissions 20%;
- Moot Court oral participation 20%.
Level of positive performance ("E") is 51%.
